386
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:20,778
Vultures are birds.

387
00:21:21,153 --> 00:21:22,193
No kidding.

388
00:21:22,318 --> 00:21:23,781
<i>Hines was a bird-watcher.</i>

389
00:21:24,141 --> 00:21:26,868
That's why he had binoculars.
He saw Jays

390
00:21:27,037 --> 00:21:28,077
<i>and Martins.</i>

391
00:21:28,246 --> 00:21:29,254
And vultures.

392
00:21:29,921 --> 00:21:31,748
Got it.
Good, so that's a dead-end.

393
00:21:32,093 --> 00:21:33,880
On the contrary,
it's a breakthrough.

394
00:21:34,005 --> 00:21:36,419
I need to speak with Gerber.
I've some questions.

395
00:21:36,587 --> 00:21:39,213
Rigsby's going to meet him.
