515
00:27:39,700 --> 00:27:41,569
Crime-fighting's hard.
Suck it up.

516
00:27:41,903 --> 00:27:43,828
- That's why we're here.
- Dooley Gerber?

517
00:27:44,256 --> 00:27:46,497
- I need to ask him a question.
- What question?

518
00:27:46,665 --> 00:27:47,816
It doesn't matter.

519
00:27:47,941 --> 00:27:50,553
Can you keep the guard off me?
Could you, please?

520
00:27:51,938 --> 00:27:52,938
It's okay.

521
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:59,719
Dooley, you can tell me.
The truth is you killed your son-in-law.

522
00:27:59,844 --> 00:28:01,144
Isn't that true?

523
00:28:03,021 --> 00:28:04,223
And who are you now?

524
00:28:05,220 --> 00:28:06,618
That's a very good answer.

525
00:28:06,743 --> 00:28:07,743
Thank you.

526
00:28:13,733 --> 00:28:14,483
So?

527
00:28:14,849 --> 00:28:16,026
What'd you learn?

528
00:28:16,195 --> 00:28:17,680
That was a control question.

529
00:28:17,805 --> 00:28:20,017
The next question I ask him
is the critical one.

530
00:28:20,324 --> 00:28:22,908
I don't need my gun.
I can just hit you with my chair.

531
00:28:23,076 --> 00:28:25,308
I think you'll find
it's bolted to the floor.

532
00:28:25,433 --> 00:28:27,773
Do you understand
what's happening to you?

533
00:28:28,485 --> 00:28:29,915
You could get a prison sentence.

534
00:28:30,693 --> 00:28:32,802
I understand
that you're keeping me in jail

535
00:28:32,927 --> 00:28:35,134
in the hopes
that you will teach me a lesson.

536
00:28:35,259 --> 00:28:38,017
- It's not gonna work.
- I am not keeping you in jail.

537
00:28:38,142 --> 00:28:39,467
The law do it.

538
00:28:39,635 --> 00:28:41,382
The law, as played by Sam Bosco.

539
00:28:41,507 --> 00:28:45,139
And you can make Sam Bosco
do anything whenever you like.

540
00:28:45,651 --> 00:28:46,575
Right.

541
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:49,853
Because he's so in love with me,
I can make him do whatever he could.

542
00:28:50,638 --> 00:28:51,638
Yes.

543
00:28:52,944 --> 00:28:54,231
I was only saying that.

544
00:28:54,399 --> 00:28:56,650
Because that's what the guys
were just saying.

545
00:28:57,325 --> 00:28:58,825
It's total nonsense.

546
00:28:59,154 --> 00:29:01,404
Sam Bosco is a happily married man.

547
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:04,158
He hasn't the faintest
interest in me that way.

548
00:29:04,554 --> 00:29:07,007
I have no influence
over him whatsoever.

549
00:29:07,132 --> 00:29:09,186
The guys noticed it, too?
I'm impressed.

550
00:29:09,311 --> 00:29:11,739
He's very recessive in his passions.

551
00:29:12,284 --> 00:29:14,418
Hard to spot
that he'd kill and die for you.

552
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:16,400
Trust me, you are way off.

553
00:29:16,999 --> 00:29:18,890
Interesting puzzle you present.

554
00:29:20,125 --> 00:29:22,325
Lies and truth all mixed together.

555
00:29:24,056 --> 00:29:24,865
Look,

556
00:29:24,990 --> 00:29:26,813
I hope we can get you
out of this mess.

557
00:29:26,938 --> 00:29:28,301
But it's also true

558
00:29:28,605 --> 00:29:31,486
that I do hope
that you learn a lesson from this.

559
00:29:31,895 --> 00:29:33,639
There are real boundaries in life.

560
00:29:33,764 --> 00:29:35,189
These are real prison walls.

561
00:29:35,357 --> 00:29:38,354
Only in your mind, Lisbon.
Only in your mind.

562
00:31:54,413 --> 00:31:55,207
Help!

563
00:31:55,332 --> 00:31:56,484
Help! Deputy!

564
00:31:56,834 --> 00:31:59,291
We got a man down, man!
He ain't moving!

565
00:31:59,459 --> 00:32:01,418
Deputy, I got a man down! Help me!

566
00:32:03,494 --> 00:32:06,090
Oh, crap.
We have an inmate down, level nine.

567
00:32:06,615 --> 00:32:08,615
Number eight out like a light.

568
00:32:09,016 --> 00:32:11,135
- Did you do this?
- No, man, I didn't touch him!

569
00:32:11,260 --> 00:32:12,810
He just ain't movin'!

570
00:32:28,715 --> 00:32:29,767
'Sup with him?

571
00:32:29,892 --> 00:32:31,907
If I know.
He was like this when I got there.

572
00:32:32,585 --> 00:32:34,788
Okay, leave him here.
I'll call the medic.

573
00:32:34,913 --> 00:32:36,728
You guys go get back on post.

574
00:32:41,840 --> 00:32:43,490
Got a customer for you.

575
00:32:46,622 --> 00:32:47,622
Okay.

576
00:32:57,639 --> 00:32:59,139
What are you saying?

577
00:33:00,868 --> 00:33:01,868
My hand.

578
00:33:03,414 --> 00:33:04,414
Hand?

579
00:33:11,559 --> 00:33:12,959
Steve, come quick.

580
00:33:14,618 --> 00:33:16,785
We got a problem, Steve.
I need help.

581
00:33:17,101 --> 00:33:18,201
I need help!

582
00:33:21,958 --> 00:33:23,331
Someone! Someone!

583
00:33:27,130 --> 00:33:28,088
Help!

584
00:33:35,293 --> 00:33:36,293
After you.

585
00:33:41,120 --> 00:33:42,120
Help!

586
00:33:42,505 --> 00:33:43,581
Somebody!

587
00:33:46,733 --> 00:33:47,779


588
00:34:02,043 --> 00:34:04,047
Lisbon, I had a horrible dream.

589
00:34:04,172 --> 00:34:06,453
I dreamt that Jane
escaped the county jail.

590
00:34:06,711 --> 00:34:09,199
I dreamt that the sheriff,
the A.G. and the district super.

591
00:34:09,324 --> 00:34:11,173
All called to yell at me.

592
00:34:12,384 --> 00:34:14,495
Now, you're gonna wake me up, yes?

593
00:34:15,071 --> 00:34:16,298
I'm sorry, sir.

594
00:34:16,423 --> 00:34:19,509
I have no excuse for him.
He is beyond out of line.

595
00:34:20,111 --> 00:34:21,511
He's blown it, all right.

596
00:34:22,159 --> 00:34:23,446
We have an A.P.B. out.

597
00:34:23,571 --> 00:34:26,406
But maybe you can contact him,
persuade him to coming quiet.

598
00:34:27,291 --> 00:34:28,732
Nobody wants him to get hurt.

599
00:34:28,901 --> 00:34:30,201
Contact him how?

600
00:34:30,429 --> 00:34:31,478
Persuade him how?

601
00:34:31,653 --> 00:34:33,580
You two are close.
He'll listen to you.

602
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:35,699
- That's very funny.
- Why is it funny?

603
00:34:35,824 --> 00:34:36,874
It just is.

604
00:34:39,345 --> 00:34:40,345
<i>Hi, Sam.</i>

605
00:34:40,998 --> 00:34:41,998
<i>It's me.</i>

606
00:34:42,158 --> 00:34:43,358
Where are you?

607
00:34:44,571 --> 00:34:45,624
<i>Dooley's house.</i>

608
00:34:45,931 --> 00:34:48,377
If you send the sheriff over,
I'll have Kirby's killer

609
00:34:48,545 --> 00:34:50,095
in ten minutes or so.

610
00:34:50,297 --> 00:34:51,797
Jane, you damn fool!

611
00:34:52,913 --> 00:34:53,913
Thank you.

612
00:34:54,175 --> 00:34:57,514
What the hell are you talking about?
You said you had Kirby's killer.

613
00:34:57,939 --> 00:35:00,389
Not yet,
but I like to be an optimist.

614
00:35:00,642 --> 00:35:03,516
You wouldn't have the makings
of a cup of tea, would you?

615
00:35:05,392 --> 00:35:07,061
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

616
00:35:10,832 --> 00:35:13,277
So listen, Roddy told me
about the vultures.

617
00:35:13,446 --> 00:35:15,081
And what he did to Kirby.

618
00:35:16,072 --> 00:35:17,821
How did you cope with that Donna?

619
00:35:18,408 --> 00:35:20,598
Your husband being
beaten by your brother?

620
00:35:20,912 --> 00:35:22,327
How did you feel about that?

621
00:35:22,900 --> 00:35:24,335
- Angry.
- With who?

622
00:35:24,633 --> 00:35:25,633
Myself,

623
00:35:26,296 --> 00:35:27,124
my family.

624
00:35:27,651 --> 00:35:29,820
Kirby was a good man,
and I let him down.

625
00:35:29,945 --> 00:35:31,695
No. No, daddy, it's true.

626
00:35:32,015 --> 00:35:34,339
I let the money blind me.
We all did.

627
00:35:34,852 --> 00:35:37,885
- Excuse me. I got stuff to do.
- Please don't go, Sandrine.

628
00:35:38,054 --> 00:35:39,740
I was just gonna say how funny it is

629
00:35:39,865 --> 00:35:42,610
When you have a big family fight,
it can clarify a situation.

630
00:35:42,894 --> 00:35:44,491
Do you think that happened at all?

631
00:35:44,616 --> 00:35:46,393
- I wish.
- Maybe Kirby

632
00:35:46,561 --> 00:35:47,655
found clarity.

633
00:35:48,149 --> 00:35:49,931
Maybe kirby realized

634
00:35:50,290 --> 00:35:52,846
how, important it was
for him to be truthful.

635
00:35:54,745 --> 00:35:56,396
When we found poor Kirby,

636
00:35:56,571 --> 00:35:58,875
he had some flecks of glitter
on his face.

637
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:01,377
And when I saw you,
Dooley, at the prison.

638
00:36:01,661 --> 00:36:03,798
You had some glitter
on your face, too.

639
00:36:04,081 --> 00:36:07,383
Which means you and Kirby
were in close contact,

640
00:36:07,860 --> 00:36:08,957
to the same woman.

641
00:36:09,270 --> 00:36:10,876
A woman who likes to wear glitter.

642
00:36:11,461 --> 00:36:13,419
That would be you, Sandrine.

643
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:17,424
- You're stupid.
- Often.

644
00:36:19,142 --> 00:36:21,470
But I now also see that neither

645
00:36:21,875 --> 00:36:23,344
Dooley nor Donna

646
00:36:24,162 --> 00:36:27,594
had any notion of this connection
between you and he.

647
00:36:27,769 --> 00:36:30,773
Which means Kirby was
very considerate...

648
00:36:31,290 --> 00:36:33,514
Considerate enough to warn you
before he came clean

649
00:36:33,639 --> 00:36:34,795
about your affair.

650
00:36:36,740 --> 00:36:38,904
I swear on my life
there was no affair.

651
00:36:39,073 --> 00:36:40,228
Sure there was.

652
00:36:40,353 --> 00:36:42,908
You were bored and frustrated.
He was available.

653
00:36:44,684 --> 00:36:46,286
Kirby soon expose you,

654
00:36:46,612 --> 00:36:48,287
and he broke it off, yes?

655
00:36:48,614 --> 00:36:50,374
He wanted to get out
of Sutter Valley.

656
00:36:50,834 --> 00:36:52,879
He wanted to start
a new life with his wife.

657
00:36:53,004 --> 00:36:54,628
The woman that he did love.

658
00:36:55,165 --> 00:36:56,547
But first he felt compelled

659
00:36:57,277 --> 00:37:00,236
to have to tell everybody the truth,
the fool.

660
00:37:00,511 --> 00:37:02,719
He was gonna ruin your life
over what...

661
00:37:02,887 --> 00:37:06,019
some birds?
For a beating that he possibly deserved.

662
00:37:06,144 --> 00:37:08,711
Why would he do that?
You begged him not to tell.

663
00:37:08,923 --> 00:37:10,123
You begged him

664
00:37:10,449 --> 00:37:11,854
and he just wouldn't listen.

665
00:37:13,256 --> 00:37:14,767
This is all a lie.

666
00:37:15,110 --> 00:37:17,708
- That never happened.
- Yeah, you had to kill him

667
00:37:17,833 --> 00:37:19,194
right there and then.

668
00:37:20,181 --> 00:37:22,573
It's a lie. It's a lie.

669
00:37:22,741 --> 00:37:26,292
I'm sorry, Sandrine, but we have
conclusive forensic evidence

670
00:37:26,417 --> 00:37:28,158
from our boys at the crime lab.

671
00:37:28,793 --> 00:37:32,124
The glitter on Kirby's face
covered in your D.N.A., covered.

672
00:37:33,073 --> 00:37:34,723
And D.N.A. doesn't lie.

673
00:37:36,734 --> 00:37:40,173
I don't know where that came from,
'cause it wasn't me.

674
00:37:40,436 --> 00:37:41,831
Police are on their way.

675
00:37:41,956 --> 00:37:44,803
I'd be honest with your family,
you may not see them for a while.

676
00:37:53,727 --> 00:37:56,179
- Oh, please!
- Tell me that it isn't true.

677
00:37:56,679 --> 00:37:58,882
He made me do it.

678
00:37:59,098 --> 00:38:01,209
- He made you do it?
- He made me do it!

679
00:38:01,334 --> 00:38:03,280
- She'll have her punishment.
- Not enough!

680
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:14,665
Patrick Jane,
we know you're in there.

681
00:38:14,834 --> 00:38:16,394
Come out with your hands up.

682
00:38:21,534 --> 00:38:23,503
It's me they're after, not you.

683
00:38:23,806 --> 00:38:25,802
And there is
no D.N.A. evidence either.

684
00:38:26,168 --> 00:38:28,597
That scientific, forensic stuff,
it's all overrated.

685
00:38:29,210 --> 00:38:31,850
Thank you for the tea.
No take-backs.

686
00:38:39,278 --> 00:38:41,593
I'm coming now! Don't shoot.

687
00:38:53,907 --> 00:38:54,907
Thank you.

688
00:39:08,454 --> 00:39:10,868
Jane got a confession
from Sandrine Gerber.

689
00:39:11,258 --> 00:39:12,358
Case closed.

690
00:39:12,886 --> 00:39:16,158
Yeah, the A.G. likely
won't make it stick, what with...

691
00:39:17,170 --> 00:39:19,363
his key witness
being in jail himself.

692
00:39:19,488 --> 00:39:23,208
In for a good, long spell
once added in the skip charges.

693
00:39:24,434 --> 00:39:26,552
That's what I wanted
to talk to you about.

694
00:39:27,130 --> 00:39:29,032
I thought this would
teach Jane a lesson.

695
00:39:29,271 --> 00:39:31,985
I thought he'd back down
or apologize, but he didn't,

696
00:39:32,110 --> 00:39:33,787
and now it's gone too far.

697
00:39:34,547 --> 00:39:35,799
You gotta let him go.

698
00:39:36,108 --> 00:39:38,625
If you drop the charges,
the A.G. won't chase it.

699
00:39:41,058 --> 00:39:42,944
What if I don't want to do that?

700
00:39:45,721 --> 00:39:47,321
Don't make me go there, Sam.

701
00:39:51,350 --> 00:39:53,432
What are you saying, exactly?

702
00:39:54,028 --> 00:39:55,623
You know what I'm saying.

703
00:39:56,722 --> 00:39:59,282
I'll talk about
what happened eight years ago.

704
00:40:03,513 --> 00:40:04,670
You'd go there?

705
00:40:06,311 --> 00:40:07,311
Really?

706
00:40:08,809 --> 00:40:11,079
- I don't believe you.
- Believe me.

707
00:40:11,312 --> 00:40:12,312
Here I am.

708
00:40:17,459 --> 00:40:19,280
You would ruin our lives,

709
00:40:19,746 --> 00:40:21,149
our careers,

710
00:40:22,161 --> 00:40:23,161
over Jane?

711
00:40:24,570 --> 00:40:26,602
Does he mean that much to you?

712
00:40:26,727 --> 00:40:28,027
He closes cases.

713
00:40:28,424 --> 00:40:30,029
"He closes cases."

714
00:40:32,126 --> 00:40:33,180
Is that all it is?

715
00:40:38,727 --> 00:40:40,780
If you don't let Jane go,

716
00:40:40,989 --> 00:40:42,481
I'll talk. That's all.

717
00:40:46,918 --> 00:40:48,288
What are you gonna do?

718
00:40:56,354 --> 00:40:57,568
Okay, you did good.

719
00:40:58,428 --> 00:40:59,952
There's 2 things puzzling me.

720
00:41:00,077 --> 00:41:02,730
How did you get out of jail,
how did you get a change of clothes?

721
00:41:02,855 --> 00:41:05,404
- I'm glad you asked that question.
- It was very...

722
00:41:07,014 --> 00:41:09,094
- ... simple.
- So they let you out, then?

723
00:41:09,730 --> 00:41:11,883
They did. Thank you very much.

724
00:41:12,651 --> 00:41:14,035
Nothing do with me.

725
00:41:14,973 --> 00:41:15,973
So modest.

726
00:41:17,535 --> 00:41:20,143
Right, Bosco's so in love with me,
he'll do whatever I say.

727
00:41:22,971 --> 00:41:24,513
It's a little far-fetched.

728
00:41:25,290 --> 00:41:27,540
He does love you. How could he not?

729
00:41:28,041 --> 00:41:31,341
But he's not the type to bend
his principles over love.

730
00:41:31,979 --> 00:41:35,659
I figure it's something more concrete.
You must have something on him.

731
00:41:36,363 --> 00:41:37,913
- You think?
- Yes.

732
00:41:38,619 --> 00:41:40,939
Something he did wrong.

733
00:41:41,278 --> 00:41:43,391
Something very bad
that you know about.

734
00:41:43,516 --> 00:41:46,216
Now he's not the type
to steal or do drugs,

735
00:41:46,514 --> 00:41:49,125
So my guess... he hurts someone.

736
00:41:51,197 --> 00:41:52,281
He killed him.

737
00:41:52,552 --> 00:41:55,269
He killed a bad guy
that he couldn't catch any other way.

738
00:41:57,336 --> 00:41:58,723
And you helped him do it.

739
00:42:00,487 --> 00:42:03,988
You found out after the fact,
and you...

740
00:42:04,712 --> 00:42:07,912
let him off the hook
because the bad guy deserved it.

741
00:42:11,067 --> 00:42:14,084
I'm touched that you would risk
your career over me.

742
00:42:14,209 --> 00:42:15,614
That means a lot to me.

743
00:42:16,439 --> 00:42:19,189
If you're right,
and I'm not saying you are,

744
00:42:19,517 --> 00:42:22,536
It would mean I broke
the trust of somebody I respect

745
00:42:22,661 --> 00:42:24,040
and admire for your sake.

746
00:42:25,557 --> 00:42:27,460
If it is true,
I would hope in the future

747
00:42:27,585 --> 00:42:31,485
you'd be a little bit more mature
and responsible in your behavior.

748
00:42:32,254 --> 00:42:35,204
I'm grateful and all that,
but let's not go crazy here.

749
00:42:35,624 --> 00:42:37,429
I should have let you rot in jail.

